[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Soda Core is a data quality and data contract verification engine.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] It lets you define data quality contracts in YAML and automatically validate both schema and data across your data stack.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Soda Core provides the Soda Command-Line Interface (CLI) and Python API, which you can use to generate, test, publish, and verify contracts.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] These operations can be executed locally during development, embedded programmatically within your data pipelines (Airflow, Dagster, Prefect, etc.), or executed remotely when connected to Soda Cloud.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] This repository hosts the open source Soda Core packages which are installable using the **Public PyPI installation flow** described in Soda's documentation.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To use Soda, you must have installed the following on your system.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Soda Core v4 open source packages are available on public PyPI and have the form `soda-{data source}`.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Replace `soda-postgres` with the appropriate package for your data source.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] For a list of supported data sources, packages, and configurations, see the data source reference for Soda Core.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Soda package names have changed with the release of version 4.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Legacy version 3 open source packages have the form `soda-core-{data source}`.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] For a list of supported data sources and other details, see the v3 documentation within this repository.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] For information about Soda Core v3, see the v3 README file and the Soda v3 online documentation.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] The examples show minimal configurations.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] For more detailed examples and explanations, see the Soda Cloud documentation.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To see detailed logs, add `--verbose` or `-v` to any of these commands.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To define a local configuration for your data source and validate the connection, run the following commands.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] By default, the YAML file generated as `ds_config.yml` is a template for PostgreSQL connections.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To learn how to populate a data source configuration file, see the data source reference for Soda Core.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Create and populate new contract YAML file.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To understand how to write a contract, see the online documentation, or the example below, which is configured to test a table or view with qualified name `db.schema.dataset` within a data source named `postgres_ds`.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] This table is assumed to have columns named `id`, `name`, and `size`.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] The data source name `postgres_ds` must match the `name` property in the data source configuration file.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To execute commands remotely, connect Sore Core to Soda Cloud.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To learn how configure Soda Cloud, see the documentation about configuring data sources and datasets and working with contracts.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] Obtain Soda Cloud credentials and add them to the Soda Cloud config file.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To generate credentials, follow this procedure.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To verify contracts via Soda Cloud using the Soda Runner (formerly known as the Soda Agent), configure a dataset and contract in Soda Cloud and configure a runner in your environment.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To obtain the Soda Cloud dataset identifier, for example `postgres_ds/db/schema/dataset`, open the contract in Soda Cloud, enable the `Toggle Code` control, and copy the identifier from the first line of the contract.
[src:soda-data-quality/main-readme-md] To view more examples of interacting with Soda Cloud using Soda Core, see the Soda documentation.
